:::summary
Love is one of the most profound and examined concepts in human experience — spanning philosophy, theology, psychology, and daily life. From the ancient Greek distinctions between *eros*, *philia*, and *agape* to the Christian proclamation that "God is love" (1 John 4:8), love has been understood as the animating force of creation and the highest calling of human beings. In Latter-day Saint theology, love is both a divine attribute and the central commandment, expressed most fully in charity — "the pure love of Christ" (Moroni 7:47).
